Just visited #Reliance SMART Super Store. It's their grocery retail chain. People here just call it Reliance Market.  Last time I visited was about 6 months ago. Saw a lot of difference today.  + Insane amount of products. Literally, everything that is needed in daily life is available. + With other popular brands, many of their own 'Good Life' branded grocery products selling well. + JioMart employees fulfilling online orders from that store itself. + Many products available at a cheaper price than other shops or online. + Decent amount of retail buyers on a Sunday afternoon, that too during #INDvsAUSfinal. + Saw many small shop owners buying stuff from there to sell it in their own shops. One told me he gets it cheaper than wholesalers.  Reliance is definitely trying to capture the retail chain market share.
